# Locations polled by aromeweather. Format: lat,lon  name
# Lines starting with '#' and blank lines are ignored.
# Each location is also inserted into the InfluxDB 'location' measurement
# so dashboards (e.g. Grafana) can resolve lat/lon back to a human name.
# Coordinates are rounded to 2 decimals by the script (~1 km resolution).
#
# This is the template. install.sh copies it to locations.conf on the
# first run only; subsequent runs leave your edited locations.conf alone
# (and locations.conf is gitignored, so 'git pull' won't clobber it).
# Edit locations.conf -- not this file -- then re-run ./install.sh.

48.78,9.18    Stuttgart
52.52,13.40   Berlin
48.86,2.35    Paris
51.51,-0.13   London
55.68,12.57   Copenhagen
